-- Factbox: Advisors on $39 billion AT&T deal for T-Mobile USA
-- 
-- Sun Mar 20, 2011 7:47pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/20/us-tmobile-att-advisors-idUSTRE72J4UG20110320

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - AT&T Inc struck a $39 billion deal to buy Deutsche Telekom AG's T-Mobile USA on Sunday, which would create a new U.S. mobile market leader. 

 The deal should also drive huge fees to the investment banks and law firms that advised the companies on the acquisition. The following banks advised AT&T on the deal: Greenhill & Co JPMorgan Chase Evercore Partners The following banks advised Deutsche Telekom on the sale: Morgan Stanley (lead financial advisor) Deutsche Bank Credit Suisse The following law firms worked for AT&T: Sullivan & Cromwell Arnold & Porter Crowell & Moring The following law firms worked for Deutsche Telekom: Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen & Katz Cleary Gottlieb Wiley Rein (Compiled by Michael Erman; Editing by  Diane Craft )